STELLENBOSCH FC have confirmed the sad passing of youngster defender Oshwin Andries. The 19- year-old centre-back passed away on Saturday. Andries made his first team debut this season against Orlando Pirates. He captained the Diski team to the DStv Diski Challenge Championship last season and his star was on the rise. He was among the outstanding players that helped the club win the English Premiership Next Generation Cup in July last year. He also captained SA Under-20 national team. Stellenbosch now confirmed the tragic news via the following statement on Saturday nigh. "It is with deep sadness that Stellenbosch F.C. has learned of the untimely passing of promising young defender, Oshwin Andries," the club announced. "The Club is not in a position to provide further information at this stage and asks that his family’s privacy is respected in this difficult time of bereavement.Andries was a gifted young footballer who graduated from the SFC Academy to make his professional debut at the age of 18. "He later became the Club’s youngest-ever goalscorer in the DStv Premiership and captained South Africa at the recent U-20 AFCON COSAFA qualifiers.His presence, both on the pitch and off it, will be sorely missed. The thoughts and prayers of everyone at Stellenbosch F.C. are with his family, friends and loved ones."